South Africa's Gauteng Province May Cut Planned Road Tolls, Star Reports

-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 
2011-02-22T05:00:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-22/south-africa-s-gauteng-province-may-cut-planned-road-tolls-star-reports.html
  South Africa ’s Gauteng province may
cut planned toll charges for the use of highways after
opposition from business and residents, Johannesburg’s Star
newspaper reported, citing George Mahlaela, director general of
the country’s national trasnsport department.  “People are saying this is too much, so, through
consultation, we will relook at the tariffs,” he said,
according to the newspaper.  Under the plan charges to be implemented could be as high
as 66 South African cents ($0.09) per kilometer.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  